üéØ Project Overview

This research explored Digital Twin technology for sustainable farming. It progressed from single-plant monitoring (2023) to complex aquaponics ecosystem management (2026), using AWS IoT services to monitor, analyze, and optimize environmental conditions for plants and fish.

Key Outcomes:
	‚Ä¢	Real-time remote monitoring of crops and aquaponics systems
	‚Ä¢	Data-driven decision-making to optimize resources and yield
	‚Ä¢	Scalable digital twin architecture adaptable to single or multi-component systems

‚∏ª

üí° What is a Digital Twin?

A Digital Twin is a virtual replica of a physical system that:
	‚Ä¢	Receives real-time data from IoT sensors
	‚Ä¢	Mirrors the system‚Äôs current state and behavior
	‚Ä¢	Enables simulation and predictive analytics
	‚Ä¢	Supports remote monitoring and control

In agriculture, it empowers farmers to optimize water, nutrients, and environmental conditions, while predicting outcomes and proactively addressing issues.

‚∏ª

üõ†Ô∏è Technical Architecture

Hardware Layer
	‚Ä¢	Raspberry Pi 4B ‚Äì Local gateway for sensor data acquisition
	‚Ä¢	Sensors (2026 system): pH, turbidity, temperature, humidity, soil moisture, light intensity
	‚Ä¢	Networking: WiFi/Ethernet to AWS Cloud
	‚Ä¢	Power: UPS backup for uninterrupted operation

Cloud Infrastructure (AWS)
	‚Ä¢	AWS IoT Core: Secure MQTT/HTTPS communication
	‚Ä¢	AWS Lambda: Serverless data processing & aggregation
	‚Ä¢	Amazon Timestream: Time-series database for sensor data
	‚Ä¢	AWS IoT TwinMaker: Digital twin modeling & 3D visualization
	‚Ä¢	Amazon Managed Grafana: Dashboards for real-time monitoring
	‚Ä¢	AWS IAM & CloudWatch: Access control, monitoring, and alerts

Software Stack
	‚Ä¢	Python 3.x ‚Äì Raspberry Pi scripts for sensor integration
	‚Ä¢	AWS ‚Äì Cloud service communication
	‚Ä¢	MQTT Protocol ‚Äì Low-latency IoT messaging
	‚Ä¢	3D Modeling: LiDAR scanning (iPhone) for accurate aquaponics replica

üìä Research Methodology

Pipeline:
	1.	Sensors record data every 30‚Äì60s
	2.	Raspberry Pi sends data to AWS IoT Core via MQTT
	3.	Lambda processes, validates, and aggregates readings
	4.	Timestream stores time-series data
	5.	TwinMaker updates digital twin
	6.	Grafana visualizes real-time and historical trends

‚∏ª

üß™ Experimental Results

2023 ‚Äì Single Plant Monitoring
	‚Ä¢	6 months of data, 50,000+ readings
	‚Ä¢	98% accuracy replicating real plant conditions
	‚Ä¢	50% reduction in water consumption
	‚Ä¢	Real-time alerts prevented plant stress

2026 ‚Äì Aquaponics Ecosystem
	‚Ä¢	Monitored fish + plant system over 6 months
	‚Ä¢	90% water savings vs traditional farming
	‚Ä¢	Multi-parameter analysis linked fish waste to plant nutrient uptake
	‚Ä¢	Predictive models guided optimal harvest times
	‚Ä¢	Real-time 3D dashboard with sensor overlays enabled proactive decisions

